[30;1m116 | [0m[35m===============[0m
[30;1m117 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m118 | [0m[35mEvery indented statement is braced; even if the block contains just one[0m
[30;1m119 | [0m[35mstatement.  The opening brace is on the line that contains the control[0m
[30;1m120 | [0m[35mflow statement that introduces the new block; the closing brace is on the[0m
[30;1m121 | [0m[35msame line as the else keyword, or on a line by itself if there is no else[0m
[30;1m122 | [0m[35mkeyword.  Example:[0m
[30;1m123 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m185 | [0m[35mWe use traditional C-style /``*`` ``*``/ comments and avoid // comments.[0m
[30;1m186 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m187 | [0m[35mRationale: The // form is valid in C99, so this is purely a matter of[0m
[30;1m188 | [0m[35mconsistency of style. The checkpatch script will warn you about this.[0m
[30;1m189 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m190 | [0m[35mMultiline comment blocks should have a row of stars on the left,[0m
[30;1m191 | [0m[35mand the initial /``*`` and terminating ``*``/ both on their own lines:[0m
